The paper deals with the convergence of products of stochastic matrices, which is a topic in both dynamical systems (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the algorithmic complexity of finding the shortest SIA product, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.SY). The paper also mentions Markov chains, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
